<br />
The only thing I can say - Sam, PP and Hobbit stealth are a good combo - And you can&#39;t go wrong with Arwen, ER - she can clean up your hand. <br />
(By the way - You can switch up Legolas, SoT and Arwen, ER for Aragorn, HttWC (just replace the KiE for another HttWC)). No matter who you are you can&#39;t doctor anything to get a great hand. <br />
Basically I am trying to set up a Fellowship to play any minions or any combo of minions. This should be very effect. <br />
<br />
Minions are expensive - so what. Play them anyway. What about the Bridge? You can always have fun at the Bridge, RUN you fools. You don&#39;t run far with Uruks. I figured Saruman can come in handy around site 4, too. Bluff your opponent - or don&#39;t - either way, you get a card out of your hand or they move... Captain is stictly for Lurtz and Saruman. Don&#39;t get all crazy and pull out some half crappy Uruk-hai(not even an Assassin or Berserker). <br />
<br />
Bid - Low or 0, let them play to your sites - yes my sites suck, but thats the whole point. Get you opponent thinking defesively make him/her play your game not theirs. The sites strictly hurt both players - it&#39;s to test versatily of decks.  That way you know how effective you can be against all deck types.<br />
<br />
Well anyway - you anyone has questions d-mail me. <br />
<br />
Zach<br />
